.TH "__device_suspend_noirq" 9 "__device_suspend_noirq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__device_suspend_noirq \- Execute a "noirq suspend" callback for given device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __device_suspend_noirq
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "pm_message_t state "  ","
.BI "bool async "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to handle.
.IP "state" 12
PM transition of the system being carried out.
.IP "async" 12
If true, the device is being suspended asynchronously.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The driver of \fIdev\fP will not receive interrupts while this function is being
executed.
